    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Door hinges fabricated with a slope on the knuckle which causes the door to rise when opened. Rising hinges are used when there are obstructions along the door's bottom edge, such as carpeting.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000027101/Smit, Means Illustrated Construction Dictionary (1985)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Bisagra de puertas fabricadas con una vertiente en la charnela la cual produce que la puerta suba cuando se abre. Bisagras con levante son usadas cuando hay impedimentos en el canto inferior de la puerta, como si está alfombrado.
</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
